def: To plead against each other, or go to trial between themselves,as the claimants in an in an interpleader. See Interpleader. [Writtenalso enterplead.]
A lamp or candlestick. [R.]By him who 'mid the golden lampads went. Trench.
A kind of stone containing native vitriol or subphate of iron,used in making ink.
Having the ventral fins beneath the throat; -- said of certainfishes.
Having, or characterized by, reliance; confident; trusting.
To proclaim with a loud voice, or by outcry, as a hawker ortown-crier does. Swift.
